cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.SE 

The paper deals with semantics of logic programs, specifically higher-order logic programs with negation. This falls under the area of logic and reasoning, which is covered by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses stratification and local stratification, which are concepts from classical logic programming, falling under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions stable model semantics, which is a concept from non-monotonic reasoning, falling under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the technique of extensional semantics, which is a concept from software engineering, falling under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
